  "summary": "n8n-nodes-quick-utils opens reverse shell to hardcoded remote host on require",
  "details": "The package's main entry (index.js) requires child_process and, on load, opens a TCP socket to the hardcoded remote endpoint 103.27.109.184:8894 and pipes the socket to interactive /bin/bash and /bin/sh processes it spawns locally, wiring the shell's stdin/stdout to the network stream. This yields full interactive remote command execution on the installer's host as soon as the module is required, which n8n does automatically when loading community nodes. The advertised n8n node functionality is an empty stub and does not correspond to the observed behavior.",
